com.huawei.ipr.pof.manager

Class PofManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.huawei.ipr.pof.manager.PofManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPMService, IFloodlightModule, IFloodlightService

    public class PofManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements IFloodlightModule, IPMService
    PofManager implements ISMService.

    PofManager is a connector to interconnect with:

    • OFMessageBypassManager for getting OFMessages from controller and to process OFMessages;
    • POFGUI to provide process methods to response user's input, and to display information in POFGUI
    • SMDatabase to store the data

    All the methods and parameters are name-self-explained.

    For the detail of OFMessages/OFInstructions/OFActions, please check POF white paper, OpenFlow documents and the source code.

    TODO For now POFGUI invokes PofManager direct. However, PofManager is better to be a language independent module so that PofManager could be connected with other applications. TODO One way is using TCP to connect with other application (such as POFGUI). Or, PofManager could be published as web service module so that any other application could invoke its interfaces.

    Author:
    Song Jian (jack.songjian@huawei.com), Huawei Technologies Co., Ltd.
